en, W., Seasonal lipid dynamics of the copepods Pseudocalanus minutus (Calanoida) and Oithona similis (Cyclopoida) in the Arctic Kongsfjorden (Svalbard) (2007) Mar. Biol, 150, pp. 445-454; Loeb, V., Siegel, V., Holm-Hansen, O., Hewitt, R., Fraser, W., Trivelpiece, W., Trivelpiece, S., Effects of sea-ice extent and krill or salp dominance on the Antarctic food web (1997) Nature (London), 387, pp. 897-900; Marr, J.W.S., The natural history and geography of the Antarctic krill (Euphausia superba Dana) (1962) Discov. Rep, 32, pp. 33-464; Mayzaud, P., The occurrence and distribution of octadecapentaenoic acid in a natural plankton population. A possible food chain index (1976) Lipids, 11, pp. 858-862; Mayzaud, P., Spatial and life-cycle changes in lipid and fatty acid structure of the Antarctic euphausiid Euphausia superba (1997) Antarctic communities: Species, structure and survival, pp. 284-294. , Edited by B. Battaglia, J. Valencia, and D.W.H. Walton. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, UK. pp; Nielsen, P., Mortensen, J., Vismann, B., Hansen, B.W., Physiological tolerance of marine calanoid copepod eggs to sulphide (2006) Mar. Ecol. Prog. Ser, 328, pp. 171-182; Peterson, B.J., Holmes, R.M., McClelland, J.W., Vörösmarty, C.J., Lammers, R.B., Shiklomanov, A.I., Shiklomanov, I.A., Rahmstorf, S., Increasing river discharge to the Arctic Ocean (2002) Science (Washington, D.C.), 298, pp. 2171-2172; Phleger, C.F., Nichols, P.D., Virtue, P., Lipids and buoyancy in Southern Ocean pteropods (1997) Lipids, 32, pp. 1093-1100; Richardson, A.J., Schoeman, D.S., Climate impact on plankton ecosystems in the Northeast Atlantic (2004) Science (Washington, D.C.), 305, pp. 1609-1613; Rigby, S., Milsom, C.V., Origins, evolution, and diversification of zooplankton (2000) Annu. Rev. Ecol. Evol. Syst, 31, pp. 293-313; Roemmich, D., McGowan, J., Climatic warming and the decline of zooplankton in the California (1995) Current. Science (Washington, D.C.), 267, pp. 1324-1326; Saito, H., Kotani, Y., Lipids of four boreal species of calanoid copepods: Origin of monoene fats of marine animals at higher trophic levels in the grazing food chain in the subarctic ocean ecosystem (2000) Mar. Chem, 71, pp. 69-82; Sargent, J.R., Henderson, R.J., Lipids (1986) The biological chemistry of marine copepods, pp. 59-108. , Edited by E.D.S. Corner and S.C.M. O'Hara. Clarendon, Oxford, UK. pp; Sargent, J.R., Gatten, R.R., Mcintosh, R., Wax esters in the marine environment - their occurrence, formation, transformation and ultimate fates (1977) Mar. Chem, 5, pp. 573-584; Smetacek, V., Nicol, S., Polar ocean ecosystems in a changing world (2005) Nature (London), 437, pp. 362-368; Stillwell, W., Wassail, S.R., Docosahexaenoic acid: Membrane properties of a unique fatty acid (2003) Chem. Phys. Lipids, 126, pp. 1-27; Stübing, D., (2004) Lipid biochemistry of Antarctic euphausiids - energetic adaptations and a critical appraisal of trophic markers, , Ph.D. thesis, Department of Marine Zoology, University of Bremen, Germany; Thibault, D., Head, E.J.H., Wheeler, P.A., Mesozooplankton in the Arctic Ocean in summer (1999) Deep-Sea Res. I, 46, pp. 1391-1415; Varpe, Ø., Piksen, Ø., Slotte, A., Meta-ecosystems and biological energy transport from ocean to coast: The ecological importance of herring migration (2005) Oecologia, 146, pp. 443-451; Vinje, T., Barents Sea-ice edge variation over the past 400 years (1998) Proceedings of the Workshop on Sea-Ice Charts of the Arctic, (949), pp. 4-6. , Seattle, Washington, 5-7 August, World Meteorological Organization, Geneva, Switzerland. WMO/TD; Vinje, T., Fram strait ice fluxes and atmospheric circulation: 1950-2000 (2001) J. Clim, 14, pp. 3508-3517; Visser, A.W., Jónasdóttir, S.H., Lipids, buoyancy and the seasonal vertical migration of Calanus finmarchicus (1999) Fish. Oceanogr, 8, pp. 100-106; Vogt, N.B., Knutsen, H., SIMCA pattern recognition classification of five infauna taxonomic groups using non-polar compounds analysed by high resol